benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails - Retrieve an account emails

covered: Valid Request: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails returns 200 with a JSON array of AccountEmail objects for valid accounts
Empty Response: 200 with empty JSON array when an account has no emails
Query Parameters: Extra parameters are ignored by the API
Authorization: 401/403 for missing or invalid authentication
Error Handling: 400 for invalid accountId format
Security: SQL injection and XSS attempts in accountId are rejected without exposing internal details
Edge Case: Non-existent but valid-format account returns empty array
Performance/Stress: Large dataset handling (1000+ emails) with acceptable response time
Resiliency: Retry on transient network failures
Availability: 503 when API service is unavailable
Backward compatibility: Legacy client header compatibility
Unicode/Special characters: Emails with special/unicode characters are correctly returned
Regression: Special characters preserved in emails
gaps: Pagination: No explicit pagination tests for large datasets (page/size navigation)
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling (e.g., 429 responses)
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation
Error payload consistency: Not all error codes have validated machine-readable error payloads beyond 400
404 semantics: Current tests use 200 with empty array for non-existent accounts; explicit 404 handling is not tested if applicable
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page/size, navigation, and edge cases like last page)
Add rate-limiting tests (429) and backoff behavior
Add caching tests (ETag, Cache-Control) and validate cache headers
Extend error payload tests to ensure consistent machine-readable error responses across all codes (e.g., 400, 401, 403, 503)
Clarify and test 404 vs 200 semantics for non-existent accounts if contract requires explicit 404
Test Accept header variations and content negotiation (e.g., application/json; charset=utf-8)
Enhance accessibility tests for error messages (machine-readable, localization support)
Automate performance tests with defined thresholds and monitoring for under load
